    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.onStop() continuing a three-player match when the present avatars are tied at max score while avatar 2 is non-present.",
      "The harness starts a real source round with avatar 2 already non-present, max_score 1, delayed PrintManager.start timers drained, then forces the two present avatars into same-frame wall deaths.",
      "Because Game.update() captures deaths.count() at frame start, avatars 3 and 1 both resolve to score 1 while non-present avatar 2 stays in deaths and resolveScores() output with score 0.",
      "Because Game.isWon() filters to present avatars, it sees only avatars 3 and 1 tied at max score and starts the next round instead of emitting end."
    ]
  },
